The pair where caught with cocaine and ephedrine worth about R2 million and an undisclosed amount of cash. JOHANNESBURG - The Hawks have arrested two men linked to a major drug bust in Bryanston.The pair where caught with cocaine and ephedrine worth about R2 million along with an undisclosed amount of cash.The Hawks narcotics enforcement bureau handcuffed the pair on Wednesday and say they'll appear in court on Friday.Spokesperson Ndivhuwo Mulamu said: Hawks members received a tip off about illegal business at the suspects dwelling in Bryanston and further investigated the matter. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)